What are Spices and Seasonings?
Spices and seasonings are dried seeds, fruits, roots, barks, or vegetable substances that primarily serve to flavor, color, or preserve food. Because they are typically used in small quantities, spices contribute minimal calories while providing significant amounts of essential micronutrients to the diet.
